CMFile - Class in io.github.thatsmusic99.configurationmaster
CMFile is the specialised configuration file used by ConfigurationMaster to carry out all of the required tasks in creating a config file.

It can be initialised by extending the class or using the provided constructors below.

You will be required to add all default values within the CMFile.loadDefaults() method, which should be added anyways due to it being an abstract method.
CMFile(Plugin, String) - Constructor for class io.github.thatsmusic99.configurationmaster.CMFile
Basic initialisation of the config file, using just the plugin and config name.
This places the file inside the plugin's data folder.
CMFile(Plugin, File, String) - Constructor for class io.github.thatsmusic99.configurationmaster.CMFile
Initialisation of the config file, using the plugin, config name and folder.
